result.execSummary:
Jasmine D Galkowski was found not guilty on all charges in this case. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jasmine D Galkowski is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:58 a.m.  Attorney Zeke Wiedenfeld in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Jasmine D. Galkowski in court.  Attorney Jeramiah Maynard in court for Jasmine D. Galkowski. State is ready to proceed.  Defense is ready to proceed.  Parties are in agreement as to the defendant having 2 prior convictions if she chooses to testify.  Trial Complaint provided to the Court by Attorney Wiedenfeld.  There are 2 child witnesses; they are present in the building; discussion regarding oath to be provided to the children when they testify.  Children to take the stand outside the presence of the jury, colloquy by Attorney Wiedenfeld and the Court to be given to the children while on the stand in the presence of the jury.  Discussion regarding statements the children being other acts evidence versus direct evidence.  Argument by Attorney Wiedenfeld.  Argument by Attorney Maynard.  Court finds the statements fall under direct evidence when questions asked are general, not in regard to specific individual circumstances.  There was a plea offer made to the defendant:  plead guilty to count #1, withheld sentence 3 years probation, no conditional jail time, other standards conditions of probation.  A lesser included charge was also offered.  Defense understands that was the offer, has not been able to convey the lesser included charge/plea offer yet.  
9:19 a.m., Short recess for Attorney Maynard to discuss offer with the defendant.
